roman_24yrs: Hello Princess!!!  Want to Chat with a Cute French guy???
Me : I suppose
roman_24yrs: why?
Me : shall I call you french guy or do you have a name?
roman_24yrs: i am roman you?
Me : Holly
roman_24yrs: nice to meet you
Me : same to you
*Cute french guy sends link to view his webcam. Wondering if he really is "cute" and "french" I click ACCEPT... big mistake... HUGE mistake, because after loading... Cute French guy is standing naked in front of the cam rubbing his Winkage. *shudders* And he wasnt even cute :(...


hmm, needless to say...now Im moving to France. The boys there are well endowed and arent the slighest bit coy.

Today was most exciting. Why? You ask. Well, let me tell you. Not only is it Thursday (the day before the day before the weekend begins :D ) but, it was also... *drum roll please* the 1st episode of the new season of SURVIVOR!

So, just like every other Thursday that Survivor is on Kristi and I eagerly sat (wearing our survivor memorabilia) and waited for it to begin... when suddenly... when the clock struck 8pm EST... it... it... STARTED!!!!

*sigh*

Holly + Jeff 4-ever + ever! te he he

 

*Jeff as in, Jeff Probst... dont worry boys- Im still on the market.

Even though I am severely depressed I feel obligated to update as not to upset my fans:

 

Today at work we were all informed that my boss (an amazingly kind man in his 60's) has liver cancer. At this point he has less than a year to live and 3% survival rate. Needless to say it was a depressing day....

http://www.cancer.org/docroot/home/index.asp 

Learn more or donate.

serendipity

n : good luck in making unexpected and fortunate discoveries.

 

I suppose meeting someone would qualify as a discovery... right?

Solipsism: n. Appealing theory that the self is the only reality (especially popular among philosophers and potheads).

In essence of the typical "blog" entry my day consisted of the following:

1) Work

2) Annoying dinner w/ child molesting  acquaintance.

3) Mildly stimulating conversation with the "King" of Jim Thorpe. *Tinge*

One plus side to having this new found appreciation for Live-Journal is that I am capable of sitting and rambling on and on about my genius and many many of my followers will feel compelled to read it daily. *buffs nails* The bitch of it though... is that... It takes alot of time to be a genius. You have to sit around doing nothing, really doing nothing.
Hmmm... Jenna talked me into joining the ranks of said Gay Bloggers. well, this is... entry number one and there are.... very few to follow. :)
